{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>The movement protein of tobamoviruses is necessary for the initial cell-to-cell movement during the early stages of a viral infection. This movement is active, and involves the interaction of the movement protein with the plasmodesmata. The movement protein possesses the ability to bind to RNA to achieve its role [[cite:PUB00005584]].</p>\n\n<p>The N terminus contains two particularly well-conserved regions, substitutions in one of these results in temperature-sensitive cell-to-cell movement. The C terminus contains three sub-regions characterised by the distributions of charged amino acid residues [[cite:PUB00005565]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"prints" {"PR00964" "MOVEMENT"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Tobamoviral movement protein", "short" "TMV_movement"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 0, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 18, "taxa" 92, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 2098, "sets" 0, "proteins" 380, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 0}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR001022", :literature {"PUB00005584" {"URL" nil, "issue" "2", "authors" ["Gafny R" "Lapidot M" "Berna A" "Holt CA" "Deom CM" "Beachy RN."], "ISO_journal" "Virology", "DOI_URL" "http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/0042-6822(92)90452-U", "medline_journal" "Virology", "title" "Effects of terminal deletion mutations on function of the movement protein of tobacco mosaic virus.", "year" 1992, "raw_pages" "499-507", "volume" "187", "ISBN" nil, "PMID" 1546450}, "PUB00005565" {"URL" nil, "issue" "2", "authors" ["Saito T" "Imai Y" "Meshi T" "Okada Y."], "ISO_journal" "Virology", "DOI_URL" nil, "medline_journal" "Virology", "title" "Interviral homologies of the 30K proteins of tobamoviruses.", "year" 1988, "raw_pages" "653-6", "vo